This paper deals with planar graphs and their planar drawings, which are topics typically studied in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of a universal set of slopes for 1-bend planar drawings suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the study of graph theory (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper's focus on establishing upper bounds on the 1-bend planar slope number suggests that it may also be relevant to the study of graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper's algorithmic approach to constructing planar drawings suggests that it may also be relevant to the study of algorithms and data structures (cs.SI).
